        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 3 at 2:44PM PDT by NWS San Diego CA</headline>
        <description>At 244 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Fontana, moving west at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Riverside, San Bernardino, Fontana, Ontario, Rialto, Chino, Redlands,
Yucaipa, Pomona, Rancho Cucamonga, Chino Hills, Upland, Highland,
Colton, Montclair, Loma Linda, Muscoy, Mentone, Rubidoux, and Hiwy
330 Between San Bernardino And Running Springs.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
